    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion and garlic have softened, add your <strong>cayenne pepper</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and <strong>tomato paste</strong> to the pan with your <strong>chicken stock mix </strong>and <strong>chipotle paste </strong>and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[300ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml]</span> <strong>boiled</strong> <strong>water</strong> and cook for 5 min or until a thick sauce remains – this is your <strong>chipotle sauce</strong></p><p>While the sauce is thickening, drain and rinse your <strong>black beans </strong>and <strong>sweetcorn</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1715602855834-x200.jpg",
